listing.name: Card QR Code
listing.description:
This Trello Power-Up displays a **QR code that contains the active card's url**. The code **can be printed and used as a physical link to the card**, or can be displayed in a mobile device to another user to quickly point them to that specific Trello card.

## Use cases

Generally, **Card QR Code can be used anywhere a physical link to the information contained in a Trello card may be useful**. Current users range from **manufacturers**, who need to associate a Trello card with a specific physical product, to **estate agents**, who need to provide potential buyers with a QR code linking to a specific property for sale or rent.

I developed this software when I began using Trello cards to store the recipes of my ferments. Rather than sticking simple labels on them, **I can print and tape on each of them the QR code of the relevant Trello card**. I can then use my phone to scan a QR code and load that ferment's Trello card. Different QR code colours help differentiate the various types of ferments.

## Free functionality

The Trello Power-Up **Card QR Code is free to use**. The free version allows you to customise the QR code colour and its size in the printout. These settings are saved for each card individually.

## Licensed version

You can purchase a licence directly within the Power-Up. In addition to the free functionality, you would be able to **edit and format the text above and below the QR code**. Additionally, while in the free version the QR code colour and size can only be defined individually for each card, a licensed version allows you to **set defaults for all the cards in the current board**. In this way you can define a common style and text for all of your QR codes.

Two types of licences are available. The first, board-based, applies to **all the users and the cards of a specific board**; the other, workspace-based, applies to **all the users and cards of all the boards in a specific workspace**.

You can **test the licensed functionality free for 21 days**. No personal or payment details are required to activate the trial.

## Configuring the text around the QR code

All the editing is done in the *Edit view* of the Power-Up, where the text is entered **using the same markup language of a standard Trello Card**. The text can include placeholders  such as `[cardname]` and `[boardname]` that are replaced, in the *Display* and *Printout* views, by the relevant values. For a full list of placeholders, please refer to the Documentation.

## Documentation

Please refer to the [Card QR Code documentation](https://blendscapes.com/trello-qrcode-docs/site/) for more information.

listing.name: Burndown Charts for Trello
listing.description:
**Burndown Charts for Trello** is a versatile Power-Up tool designed for Agile teams, allowing them to track sprint progress with interactive burndown charts. Manage sprints, analyze performance, and generate reports – all directly in Trello!
![Dashboard](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/dashboard.gif)

---

## Why Choose **Burndown Charts for Trello**?

- **Burndown charts at your fingertips**
    
    Automatically generate charts that visualize team progress and help identify potential delays.

- **Create sprints in seconds**

  Define sprint details such as name, task capacity, start and end dates, and key excluded days.
  
  ![Create Sprint](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/create_sprint.gif)

- **Trello Integration**

  The app works directly in Trello, using your board data. Authorization is required only on the chart page.
  
  ![Burndown chart](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/auth.gif)

- **Flexibility and customization**

  Edit sprint details, adjust remaining capacity, and manage your schedule.
  
  ![Edit Sprint](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/edit_sprint.gif)

- **Advanced reporting**

  Download charts as PDFs in either landscape or portrait orientation – perfect for presentations and documentation.
  
  ![Download Pdf](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/download_pdf.gif)

---

## Key Features

- **Create sprints:** 
 
   Add a sprint using an intuitive form, where you can define both task capacity.
  
    ![Create Sprint](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/create_sprint.gif)

- **Visualize progress:** 
    
    Click on the sprint name in the sidebar to view the details and burndown chart.

- **Edit sprints:** 
    
    Modify details through the options available in the sidebar or within the sprint details view.

  ![Edit Sprint](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/edit_sprint.gif)

- **Delete sprints:** 
    
    Remove a sprint by confirming the action in a simple modal.

  ![Delete Sprint](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/delete_sprint.gif)

- **Export charts:** 
    
    Generate PDF reports and adjust the chart orientation.
  
    ![Download Pdf](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/download_pdf.gif)

- **Manage days:** 
    
    Exclude specific days (e.g., weekends) from the sprint.
  
    ![Manage days](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/excluded_dates.gif)

- **Settings:** 
    
    Manage users and app access in the dedicated settings section.

  ![Settings](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/settings.gif)
---

## Incoming Features

- **User management:** In the "Settings" section, you will soon be able to manage users who have access to the app.
- **Story points in capacity:** You will soon be able to define story points in the capacity field for your sprints, providing better tracking of progress.
---

## Getting Started

1. **Log in to Trello** and install Burndown Charts for Trello from the [Trello Marketplace](https://trello.com/power-ups).

2. **Add a sprint:** 

    In the sidebar, click "New Sprint +" and fill in the details, specifying task capacity.

   ![Sidebar](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/sidebar.gif)

3. **View the chart:** 
    
    Click on the sprint name in the sidebar to access the chart view.

4. **Download the report:** 
    
    Click "Download to PDF" on the chart page and select the report orientation.
   
    ![Download Pdf](https://bdc.waybacklab.app/video/gif/download_pdf.gif)
---

## Who Can Use Burndown Charts for Trello?

The app is ideal for:
- Scrum masters and Agile team leaders,
- Development teams managing sprints,
- Anyone looking to streamline their processes in Trello and track team performance.
---

## Get Started Now!

Install Burndown Charts for Trello on your Trello board and take your sprint management to the next level!
